1
00:00:11,040 --> 00:00:14,240
♫ When romance is too insignificant ♫

2
00:00:14,240 --> 00:00:21,680
♫ But I can't stop missing you, like a bad cold ♫

3
00:00:21,680 --> 00:00:28,370
♫ Drifting in a deserted island, where feelings have no reception ♫

4
00:00:28,370 --> 00:00:32,150
♫ Have you been well? ♫

5
00:00:32,150 --> 00:00:36,390
♫ Don't worry, I'll be fine ♫

6
00:00:36,390 --> 00:00:39,490
♫ Don't worry, I can't fall asleep ♫

7
00:00:39,490 --> 00:00:46,950
♫ Don't worry, I can't get used to this lonely world ♫

8
00:00:46,950 --> 00:00:53,740
♫ Hitting the pause button, leaving your side ♫

9
00:00:53,740 --> 00:01:00,790
♫ Letting the memories migrate to that day of happiness ♫

10
00:01:00,790 --> 00:01:07,100
♫ I'm trying hard to smile as I say goodbye to you ♫

11
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:12,990
♫ I recall and long for the happiness you want, I can make it happen ♫

12
00:01:12,990 --> 00:01:16,070
♫ Can't hold back the tears, leading to regret ♫

13
00:01:16,070 --> 00:01:22,160
♫ Losing you whom I love, heartbreak is inevitable ♫

14
00:01:22,160 --> 00:01:28,690
♫ I choose to bid farewell with a smile ♫

15
00:01:28,690 --> 00:01:31,170
[Lost Romance]

16
00:01:31,170 --> 00:01:33,700
Zheng Xiao'en, why didn't you show up as promised?

17
00:01:33,700 --> 00:01:36,940
I trusted you, yet you chose to run away just as we were getting started.

18
00:01:36,940 --> 00:01:41,790
If you’re such an irresponsible person, I'll be very disappointed.

19
00:01:41,790 --> 00:01:45,220
The day Tianxing transferred hospitals, you were the person he grabbed on the stretcher.

20
00:01:45,220 --> 00:01:47,690
Could this all just be a coincidence?

21
00:01:47,690 --> 00:01:49,240
It's fate.

22
00:01:49,240 --> 00:01:51,350
CEO, if I win,

23
00:01:51,350 --> 00:01:54,950
can I make a wish to have a pair of cufflinks you wear often?

24
00:01:54,950 --> 00:01:56,020
Are you okay?

25
00:01:56,020 --> 00:02:00,210
I'm actually... on the brink of collapsing.

26
00:02:00,210 --> 00:02:03,090
I used to think that we were people from different worlds,

27
00:02:03,090 --> 00:02:05,300
but the more I come to understand you,

28
00:02:05,300 --> 00:02:10,240
the more I feel that you're not that far out of reach after all.

29
00:02:10,240 --> 00:02:11,760
I will help you.

30
00:02:11,760 --> 00:02:15,340
But since I'm helping you out,

31
00:02:15,340 --> 00:02:18,240
I'd like to kindly ask you to help me with something.

32
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:23,150
Kick He Tianxing off the board of directors.

33
00:02:28,190 --> 00:02:35,270
[Lost Romance]

34
00:02:35,270 --> 00:02:37,590
[Chapter Nineteen]

35
00:02:41,570 --> 00:02:44,290
I understand what you mean, Uncle Hu.

36
00:02:45,420 --> 00:02:48,260
Sure enough, you are intelligent, Miss.

37
00:02:48,260 --> 00:02:53,180
You're the only one in the He Family who has the ability to take over Tianliang.

38
00:02:53,180 --> 00:02:54,800
Here.

39
00:03:05,070 --> 00:03:07,970
Excuse me. I need to go to the restroom.

40
00:03:11,900 --> 00:03:14,870
- He left?
- He went to the restroom.

41
00:03:14,870 --> 00:03:19,800
So... was this how he persuaded you back then?

42
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:21,770
When Dad collapsed

43
00:03:21,770 --> 00:03:25,430
and you suddenly called a board meeting to reelect the chairman,

44
00:03:25,430 --> 00:03:27,080
was it also like this?

45
00:03:27,080 --> 00:03:29,090
It was all agreed on beforehand?

46
00:03:32,020 --> 00:03:34,180
I was careless back then.

47
00:03:35,670 --> 00:03:38,550
Hu Chaoqin knows our weaknesses too well.

48
00:03:38,550 --> 00:03:40,760
That's how he was able to strike us down one by one.

49
00:03:40,760 --> 00:03:43,250
First, he eliminated you, the hardest to deal with.

50
00:03:43,250 --> 00:03:45,240
Then he had Tianjian and me fight against each other.

51
00:03:45,240 --> 00:03:48,650
Lastly, he got rid of Tianjian.

52
00:03:48,650 --> 00:03:51,290
Fool me once, shame on you.

53
00:03:51,290 --> 00:03:55,120
Fool me twice, shame on me.

54
00:04:05,750 --> 00:04:07,330
Hello?

55
00:04:16,160 --> 00:04:18,250
He's not back yet?

56
00:04:18,250 --> 00:04:20,260
Not yet.

57
00:04:28,630 --> 00:04:30,970
He's finally back.

58
00:04:37,610 --> 00:04:39,170
How's it going? Did you find it?

59
00:04:39,170 --> 00:04:41,050
This old fox sure knows how to hide things.

60
00:04:41,050 --> 00:04:43,180
Where did he hide the account book?

61
00:04:43,180 --> 00:04:46,530
Keep looking. We don't have much time left.

62
00:04:47,680 --> 00:04:49,540
Bye bye.

63
00:04:58,900 --> 00:05:01,830
D-Director Hu! Weren't you having a meal with Miss?

64
00:05:01,830 --> 00:05:05,600
Dang, he's back! Let's leave, hurry!

65
00:05:08,850 --> 00:05:11,420
Director Hu, I'll get back to work then.

66
00:05:13,020 --> 00:05:15,000
Excuse me.

67
00:05:16,130 --> 00:05:19,510
Director Hu, you first.

68
00:05:22,940 --> 00:05:25,030
Sorry.

69
00:05:38,670 --> 00:05:41,400
Hello, Miss.

70
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:44,360
Yes, I didn't get a chance to tell you.

71
00:05:44,360 --> 00:05:46,220
Please excuse my poor manners.

72
00:05:46,220 --> 00:05:48,160
No, it wasn't an urgent emergency.

73
00:05:48,160 --> 00:05:52,420
Yes, I just had to take care of some things.

74
00:05:52,420 --> 00:05:54,140
No secret account book?

75
00:05:54,140 --> 00:05:57,270
No. We looked everywhere we could.

76
00:05:57,270 --> 00:06:00,150
Nothing came out of the auditing we did earlier.

77
00:06:00,150 --> 00:06:03,480
At least on the surface, there doesn't seem to be any flaws in the accounts.

78
00:06:04,120 --> 00:06:07,240
Director Hu is more cautious than we thought.

79
00:06:11,890 --> 00:06:14,380
Hurry and pick up the trash.

80
00:06:14,380 --> 00:06:17,540
This isn't even mine; it's Old Hu's.

81
00:06:18,350 --> 00:06:21,050
What do you mean?

82
00:06:21,050 --> 00:06:22,940
When Old Hu was coming back to the office,

83
00:06:22,940 --> 00:06:24,550
I accidentally kicked over the trash can.

84
00:06:24,550 --> 00:06:28,050
I was scared there wasn't enough time, so after picking up the trash, I stuffed it in my pocket instead.

85
00:06:30,260 --> 00:06:32,020
Wait.

86
00:06:33,930 --> 00:06:37,120
[Blaze of Colors Florist Invoice]

87
00:06:41,920 --> 00:06:43,800
This is an invoice from a flower shop.

88
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:45,380
Based on this,

89
00:06:45,380 --> 00:06:49,360
we can see that Hu Chaoqin sent a flower basket to Caijing Gallery five different times.

90
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:52,470
So Old Hu loves art?

91
00:06:52,470 --> 00:06:56,280
I've known him for so long, yet I never knew about this.

92
00:06:59,840 --> 00:07:02,890
I think we need to visit Caijing Gallery.

93
00:07:02,890 --> 00:07:04,480
I'll go.

94
00:07:04,480 --> 00:07:08,630
No, it can't be someone recognizable from the company.

95
00:07:08,630 --> 00:07:13,290
Then where should we find a stranger?

96
00:07:21,600 --> 00:07:25,060
Two minutes until three, arrived right on time.

97
00:07:25,060 --> 00:07:30,060
[CEO He Tianxing]

98
00:07:35,200 --> 00:07:37,200
Come in.

99
00:07:38,460 --> 00:07:40,360
Hello.

100
00:07:49,320 --> 00:07:52,780
You are... Chief Editor Yao.

101
00:07:52,780 --> 00:07:54,420
Yes.

102
00:07:55,060 --> 00:07:56,690
Where's Zheng Xiao'en?

103
00:07:56,690 --> 00:07:59,290
She had a personal matter today.

104
00:08:01,250 --> 00:08:03,840
Last time, it was Lin Chuntian.

105
00:08:03,840 --> 00:08:05,640
This time, it's you.

106
00:08:06,530 --> 00:08:09,640
Is standing someone up your company's culture?

107
00:08:09,640 --> 00:08:12,440
Give me a reason that I can accept.

108
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:24,100
Are you okay? You seem very tired.

109
00:08:25,030 --> 00:08:27,480
I'm fine.

110
00:08:27,480 --> 00:08:29,780
The orphanage director has been sick for so many years.

111
00:08:29,780 --> 00:08:32,510
Now that she's been freed from her suffering,

112
00:08:33,320 --> 00:08:36,180
I'm actually happy for her.

113
00:08:36,180 --> 00:08:40,100
She's finally not in pain anymore.

114
00:08:40,100 --> 00:08:43,440
Really? You don't have to put up a front.

115
00:08:44,460 --> 00:08:46,790
Really.

116
00:08:46,790 --> 00:08:50,640
I'm sure she's already become an angel

117
00:08:51,500 --> 00:08:53,990
and is watching over me from heaven.

118
00:08:56,520 --> 00:08:59,640
Orphanage Director, no matter where you are,

119
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:02,420
you'll always be the brightest star.

120
00:09:10,950 --> 00:09:14,530
You! It's you, isn't it?

121
00:09:15,150 --> 00:09:18,000
You must always watch over me.

122
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:19,660
She definitely will.

123
00:09:19,660 --> 00:09:23,210
You're so considerate. You always paid her a visit whenever you had a chance.

124
00:09:23,210 --> 00:09:25,190
She'll definitely watch over you

125
00:09:25,190 --> 00:09:26,940
so that you'll always get a seat when you take the bus,

126
00:09:26,940 --> 00:09:29,000
you'll always get a free upgrade when you buy a plane ticket,

127
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:30,790
you'll be the sole winner of the lottery,

128
00:09:30,790 --> 00:09:34,060
and the parents of the overbearing CEO who loves you will have passed away.

129
00:09:34,090 --> 00:09:35,660
(So she doesn't have to deal with in-laws.)

130
00:09:35,660 --> 00:09:38,060
Isn't that being too greedy?

131
00:09:45,090 --> 00:09:46,460
What is it?

132
00:09:46,460 --> 00:09:48,820
What time is it already? The printing shop is calling.

133
00:09:48,820 --> 00:09:51,230
It must have run into problems again.

134
00:09:51,230 --> 00:09:52,760
Get to work then.

135
00:09:52,760 --> 00:09:54,460
What about you?

136
00:09:54,460 --> 00:09:56,490
I'll be okay on my own.

137
00:09:56,490 --> 00:09:57,760
Really?

138
00:09:57,760 --> 00:10:00,460
Really. Go ahead.

139
00:10:01,930 --> 00:10:03,840
Hello? I am.

140
00:10:03,840 --> 00:10:06,600
Okay, I'll go over right now.

141
00:10:09,580 --> 00:10:14,140
Zheng Xiao'en, I love you.

142
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:34,700
CEO, Xiao'en has a really important matter today,

143
00:10:34,700 --> 00:10:37,980
so she's unable to be here.

144
00:10:38,460 --> 00:10:41,200
Xiao'en grew up at an orphanage.

145
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:44,540
It's the orphanage director's birthday next week.

146
00:10:44,540 --> 00:10:48,060
She had already requested time off to celebrate with her.

147
00:10:48,060 --> 00:10:53,290
Who knew that she would suddenly pass away today?

148
00:11:07,850 --> 00:11:10,040
Where did she go?

149
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:22,580
I am He Tianxing.

150
00:11:22,580 --> 00:11:24,610
Where is Zheng Xiao'en?

151
00:11:27,140 --> 00:11:30,720
CEO, she just went home.

152
00:11:30,720 --> 00:11:32,400
She's not at home.

153
00:11:32,400 --> 00:11:35,400
Could she still be at the hospital?

154
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:37,580
I shouldn't have left her on her own.

155
00:11:37,580 --> 00:11:40,850
She must be heartbroken since the orphanage director passed away.

156
00:11:40,850 --> 00:11:44,340
As her only friend, I'm not by her side.

157
00:11:44,340 --> 00:11:47,140
Hello? Hello?

158
00:11:49,770 --> 00:11:53,050
[Everan Hospital]

159
00:11:56,130 --> 00:11:58,330
Where did you go?

160
00:12:00,400 --> 00:12:02,110
I was abandoned at a park.

161
00:12:02,110 --> 00:12:04,810
I grew up at an orphanage.

162
00:12:04,810 --> 00:12:06,980
Which orphanage?

163
00:12:06,980 --> 00:12:09,280
Yongxin Orphanage.

164
00:12:12,040 --> 00:12:18,000
Three... four... five.

165
00:12:20,340 --> 00:12:24,620
Wow, I was this tall at six years old?

166
00:12:30,060 --> 00:12:32,090
Who is it?

167
00:12:40,710 --> 00:12:42,260
It's me.

168
00:12:42,260 --> 00:12:43,960
It's me.

169
00:12:47,710 --> 00:12:50,050
I finally found you.

170
00:13:24,090 --> 00:13:28,000
I'm sure Chuntian already asked you,

171
00:13:29,910 --> 00:13:34,440
but I still want to confirm it for myself.

172
00:13:38,240 --> 00:13:42,520
Are you okay?

173
00:13:45,260 --> 00:13:47,880
I don't know why,

174
00:13:47,880 --> 00:13:51,230
but after the orphanage director passed away,

175
00:13:51,230 --> 00:13:54,710
I feel as if

176
00:13:54,710 --> 00:13:58,610
my past has been completely erased.

177
00:14:03,440 --> 00:14:05,110
After the orphanage shut down,

178
00:14:05,110 --> 00:14:08,280
all our information disappeared with it.

179
00:14:10,070 --> 00:14:13,180
The only person who remembers how I came here

180
00:14:13,180 --> 00:14:17,310
and how I grew up was the director, who's also gone.

181
00:14:19,190 --> 00:14:21,990
My childhood

182
00:14:22,440 --> 00:14:25,580
seems to have been deleted completely

183
00:14:25,580 --> 00:14:28,090
with the press of a button today.

184
00:14:36,420 --> 00:14:38,780
I understand that feeling.

185
00:14:42,640 --> 00:14:45,210
Ever since my mom passed away,

186
00:14:45,770 --> 00:14:48,200
it seems like a period was drawn

187
00:14:50,450 --> 00:14:55,430
to end my childhood that day.

188
00:15:04,780 --> 00:15:08,170
Do you still remember things from when you were young?

189
00:15:08,170 --> 00:15:10,490
I want to hear you talk about them.

190
00:15:14,070 --> 00:15:17,460
My childhood is really boring. You won't want to hear about it.

191
00:15:19,170 --> 00:15:23,420
As long as it's about you, I'll want to hear about it.

192
00:15:23,420 --> 00:15:25,540
The more, the better.

193
00:15:26,960 --> 00:15:31,890
Because as long as there's still someone in this world

194
00:15:31,890 --> 00:15:35,310
who remembers those things,

195
00:15:36,470 --> 00:15:40,990
your childhood will never be erased.

196
00:15:42,900 --> 00:15:45,960
You're willing to remember these things for me?

197
00:15:54,670 --> 00:15:59,720
I remember I participated in a singing competition when I was a kid.

198
00:15:59,720 --> 00:16:02,060
Someone chose the same song as I did.

199
00:16:02,060 --> 00:16:04,560
In the end, she got first place.

200
00:16:04,560 --> 00:16:06,590
I got second place.

201
00:16:06,590 --> 00:16:09,730
The orphanage director said I sang it best,

202
00:16:09,730 --> 00:16:12,240
but her dance was better.

203
00:16:15,120 --> 00:16:17,110
Wasn't it a singing competition?

204
00:16:17,110 --> 00:16:19,210
It's not like it was a dancing competition.

205
00:16:19,210 --> 00:16:23,060
First place should've gone to the one who sang it best.

206
00:16:23,060 --> 00:16:24,970
Right?

207
00:16:26,780 --> 00:16:31,180
She was pretty and also the class leader.

208
00:16:31,180 --> 00:16:33,770
She had parents who loved her,

209
00:16:33,770 --> 00:16:35,990
and I...

210
00:16:50,240 --> 00:16:52,280
I, He Tianxing,

211
00:16:52,840 --> 00:16:55,070
hereby announce that

212
00:16:55,070 --> 00:16:59,670
the winner of this children's singing competition is...

213
00:16:59,670 --> 00:17:03,240
Zheng Xiao'en.

214
00:17:06,110 --> 00:17:09,200
Hello, teachers, family members...

215
00:17:13,470 --> 00:17:19,020
Hello, teachers and classmates.

216
00:17:19,020 --> 00:17:21,220
I am Situ Aoran.

217
00:17:22,160 --> 00:17:25,030
What I want to share with everyone today is

218
00:17:25,030 --> 00:17:27,670
if I had a superpower...

219
00:17:32,910 --> 00:17:35,750
Not just this singing competition,

220
00:17:35,750 --> 00:17:39,970
no matter what competition it is, the winner is Zheng Xiao'en.

221
00:17:42,540 --> 00:17:44,240
It can only be Zheng Xiao'en.

222
00:17:44,240 --> 00:17:46,350
It can't be anyone else.

223
00:17:46,350 --> 00:17:48,100
What I say goes.

224
00:17:51,190 --> 00:17:53,970
Our Aoran is so great.

225
00:17:53,970 --> 00:17:57,000
Hey, that's my husband.

226
00:18:10,170 --> 00:18:13,650
Congratulations. You're the best.

227
00:18:14,870 --> 00:18:17,380
You're number one in the whole world.

228
00:18:17,380 --> 00:18:20,090
He's number one in the whole world.

229
00:18:20,090 --> 00:18:24,980
No, number one in the whole universe.

230
00:18:28,050 --> 00:18:31,500
No, number one in the whole universe.

231
00:18:31,500 --> 00:18:36,790
♫ Silently frozen like a statue ♫

232
00:18:36,790 --> 00:18:43,970
♫ The smile hollows out the shell ♫

233
00:18:43,970 --> 00:18:50,370
♫ Is the overdue promise to be discarded? ♫

234
00:18:50,370 --> 00:18:58,040
♫ Like a sugar-coated lie ♫

235
00:18:58,040 --> 00:19:03,240
♫ Brightly yet quietly shouted ♫

236
00:19:03,240 --> 00:19:04,740
What's wrong?

237
00:19:04,740 --> 00:19:08,000
Don't be so nice to me.

238
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:10,850
What's wrong? Weren't we fine just now?

239
00:19:10,850 --> 00:19:13,400
I already said, don't be so nice to me.

240
00:19:13,400 --> 00:19:15,940
Can you stay away from me?

241
00:19:19,460 --> 00:19:21,100
Why?

242
00:19:22,570 --> 00:19:26,740
Don't be like this. Don't make me confused.

243
00:19:26,740 --> 00:19:28,590
Don't...

244
00:19:28,590 --> 00:19:31,600
♫ Got nothing but time ♫

245
00:19:31,600 --> 00:19:38,580
♫ I will accompany you in insomnia ♫

246
00:19:38,580 --> 00:19:40,430
♫ You don't need to face everything alone ♫

247
00:19:40,430 --> 00:19:43,210
Don't make me fall in love with you.

248
00:19:49,320 --> 00:19:51,910
You're the one who confused me first.

249
00:19:54,040 --> 00:19:56,090
Who was the one who first spied on me,

250
00:19:56,090 --> 00:19:57,840
got close to me,

251
00:19:57,840 --> 00:20:00,120
prayed for me when I got hurt,

252
00:20:00,120 --> 00:20:02,460
and cried for me when something happened to me?

253
00:20:02,460 --> 00:20:04,580
Who was it?

254
00:20:07,060 --> 00:20:10,090
You. It was you.

255
00:20:12,490 --> 00:20:14,510
You've done so much for me,

256
00:20:14,510 --> 00:20:18,570
and now you're telling me that you don't want to fall in love with me?

257
00:20:25,770 --> 00:20:29,670
Okay, that's fine.

258
00:20:29,670 --> 00:20:31,700
You don't love me?

259
00:20:31,700 --> 00:20:33,820
Then let me love you.

260
00:20:42,450 --> 00:20:45,900
I used to think that I had a heart of stone,

261
00:20:45,900 --> 00:20:47,940
that I was invulnerable.

262
00:20:49,310 --> 00:20:51,240
Until I met you.

263
00:20:52,490 --> 00:20:55,740
The way you gazed at me made me realize

264
00:20:56,370 --> 00:20:58,940
that all of my strength in the past

265
